                                         JOHANNESBURG - A man who is suspected to have been involved in the robbery of a jewellery shop in Tshwane has been arrested.  Police say the man was found at the Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital on Thursday night while seeking medical attention.  It is understood that seven gunmen entered a store on Thursday at the Grove Mall. Shots were exchanged between the criminals and the owner of the store. Police found the suspect being treated for gunshot wounds both on the lower and upper body. The police's Daniel Mavimbela says: “He was arrested at the Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital last night while seeking medical attention. He will be charged with robbery with aggravated circumstances. He will appear in the Pretoria magistrates court soon.” (Edited by Shimoney Regter)